-- RHB Bank Said to Consider Dollar Bond Sale After Investor Talks
-- B y   T a n y a   A n g e r e r
-- 2012-05-02T01:30:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-02/rhb-bank-said-to-consider-dollar-bond-sale-after-investor-talks.html
RHB Bank Berhad hired Bank of America
Merrill Lynch, Citigroup Inc. and RHB Investment Bank Berhad to
arrange meetings with bond investors in Singapore and  Hong Kong 
from tomorrow, according to a person familiar with the matter.  The bank may seek to sell U.S. dollar bonds after the talks,
the person said, asking not to be named as the details are
private.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tanya Angerer in Singapore at 
 tangerer@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah McDonald at 
 smcdonald23@bloomberg.net  